      "data": {
        "title": "Read The Address First",
        "body": "The large address field tells you what graph you are actually in. A `github://...` address means you are reading a GitHub-backed artifact path. A local or untitled address means the save and trust story is different.  Graphs are also addressable via http (that is, you can publish it as you would a web page).",
        "tag": "Concept",
