      "data": {
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "tutorial-interface-browser-bar"
        },
        "markdown": "## Quick browser-bar checklist\n\nBefore you edit a graph, ask:\n\n- What address am I actually on?\n- Is this `github://`, local, or temporary?\n- Do I trust back, home, and refresh to get me out again?\n- What is the zoom or position indicator telling me, and can it recenter me on the root node?\n- If I need onboarding, is the handshake button on the right side of the address bar where I expect it to be?\n- If I need save actions, is the document-actions menu on the right side of the address bar enough?\n- Do I need the GitHub lesson, or just this interface lesson?\n\nThe browser bar is one of Twilite's main trust surfaces.",
        "_placement": {
          "version": 1,
          "state": "auto-placed",
          "source": "layout",
          "updatedAt": 1781373633658,
          "reason": "auto-layout"
        }
      }
    },
